SKILL|openhue|"Control Philips Hue lights, scenes, rooms via OpenHue CLI."
STEP|1|"Turn on/off the lights"
STEP|2|"Dim the living room lights"
STEP|3|"Set a scene" or "movie mode"
STEP|4|Controlling specific Hue rooms, zones, or individual bulbs
STEP|5|Adjusting brightness, color, or color temperature
STEP|6|Bridge must be on the same local network as the machine running Hermes
STEP|7|First run requires physically pressing the button on the Hue Bridge to authorize
STEP|8|Colors only work on color-capable bulbs (not white-only models)
STEP|9|Light and room names are case-sensitive — use `openhue get light` to check exact names
STEP|10|Works great with cron jobs for scheduled lighting (e.g. dim at bedtime, bright at wake)
PIT|Bridge must be on the same local network as the machine running Hermes
PIT|First run requires physically pressing the button on the Hue Bridge to authorize
PIT|Colors only work on color-capable bulbs (not white-only models)
PIT|Light and room names are case-sensitive — use `openhue get light` to check exact names
